'''Johann Kaspar Mörikofer''' (11 October 1799, in [[Frauenfeld]] &ndash; 17 October 1877, in [[Riesbach]]) was a [[Swiss people|Swiss]] [[literary history|literary]] and [[church history|ecclesiastical historian]].

==Biography==
He studied [[theology]] at the [[Carolinum, Zürich|Carolinum in Zürich]], and from 1822 to 1851 was provisor and [[rector (academia)|rector]] of city schools in [[Frauenfeld]]. From 1851 to 1869 he served as a pastor in [[Gottlieben]]. He obtained honorary doctorates at the universities of [[University of Zürich|Zürich]] (PhD, 1872) and [[University of Basel|Basel]] (theology, 1876).<ref>[http://www.hls-dhs-dss.ch/textes/d/D10760.php Mörikofer, Johann Kaspar] Historischen Lexikon der Schweiz</ref>

==Works==
His historical works have scientific value and literary charm; they include:
*''Die schweizerische Mundart im Verhältnis zur hochdeutschen Schriftsprache'' (1838) &ndash; The Swiss dialect in relation to the [[High German]] written language.
*''Klopstock in Zürich im Jahre 1750-1751'' (1851) &ndash; [[Friedrich Gottlieb Klopstock]] in Zürich in the years 1750/51. 
*''Die schweizerische Litteratur des 18. Jarhunderts'' (1861) &ndash; [[Swiss literature]] in the 18th century.
*''Ulrich Zwingli: Nach den urkundlichen Quellen'' (1867–69) &ndash; [[Ulrich Zwingli]]: According to documentary sources.
*''Geschichte der evangelischen Flüchtlinge in der Schweiz'' (1876) &ndash; History of Protestant refugees In Switzerland.

