'''Koh Se-kai''' ({{zh|t=許世楷|p=Xǔ Shìkǎi|w=Hsu3 Shih4-kai3|poj=Khó͘ Sè-khái}}; born 1934 in [[Changhua County]]) is a [[Taiwanese people|Taiwanese]] historian, politician, and [[diplomat]]. He is an important leader of the [[Taiwan independence]] movement. In 2004, Koh was appointed to be the [[Republic of China]]’s top representative to [[Japan]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Envoy to Tokyo defends policy toward Japan |url=http://www.taipeitimes.com/News/taiwan/archives/2005/03/24/2003247534 |work=[[Taipei Times]] |date=24 March 2005 |accessdate=7 March 2011 }}</ref> By June 2008, Koh had retired.

