'''Robert George Arns''' is an American [[physicist]] and [[historian]] of electrical history.
Arns was a professor at the [[University of Vermont]]. He has a Ph.D. from the [[University of Michigan]].<ref>[http://www.uvm.edu/~physics/?Page=faculty_rarns.php University of Vermont info page on Arns]</ref>
==Notable works==
* R. G. Arns, "The other transistor: early history of the [[MOSFET|metal-oxide-semiconductor field-effect transistor]]," Engineering Science and Education Journal, 7, No. 5 (October, 1998): 233-240 * R. G. Arns, "The High-Vacuum X-ray Tube: Technological Change in Social Context," [[Technology and Culture]], 38, No. 4 (October, 1997):852-90
